Only a portion of this old piece of parchment is legible. The writing on it is sloppy and looks as if it was penned hurriedly. The part you can make out reads - 

"It is foretold that only the one who bares the weight of his sins can know his desire to return, his need to consume, and thus it is that only the one may reveal the path and lead him to his rightful place among us and though the vale that cloaks the path will succumb to the one so shall the one succumb to the vale, and in giving life for life so shall his champion return to us and usher in his new reign of terrible glory."
